    public interface EventAware
extends com.guidewire.pl.domain.messaging.gen.EventAwareStubI
    Interface for beans with which one or more events can be associated. When a bundle containing an EventAwareBean is committed, any events associated with the bean are fired, which means that the "Event Messages" rule set is invoked for each of the associated events.

    EventAwareBeans have three standard events that are fired automatically: one for bean additions, one for bean removals, and one for bean changes/updates. Any number of additional events may also be defined for an EventAwareBean; these custom events can be associated with a bean using addEvent(String).
